OL,3,CInside Italy's 'toxic town', where
OL,4,Cchildren grow up fearing cancer
OL,6,FAlison told the room: "I think what
OL,7,Fyou've just said really hits home,
OL,8,Fbecause it's exactly the same as what
OL,9,Fwe have.
OL,11,F"So, in our local hospital, they
OL,12,Fpointed out, 'Why are there so many
OL,13,Fchildren and young people from Corby
OL,14,Fwho are getting rare cancers?'"
OL,16,FMiriam's mother, Antonella, also spoke
OL,17,Fof her anger.
