OL,3,CInside Italy's 'toxic town', where
OL,4,Cchildren grow up fearing cancer
OL,6,FIt was a landmark case, linking birth
OL,7,Fdefects to airborne toxic waste. Other
OL,8,Ffamilies in the town are now
OL,9,Fquestioning whether the contamination
OL,10,Fhas caused much wider health problems.
OL,12,FAlison and Andy have visited Taranto's
OL,13,Flargest hospital to help prove it.
OL,15,FAt Santissima Annunziata, they, and
OL,16,FITV News, were told an extra
OL,17,Fchildren's ward opened in 2019, in
OL,18,Fpart because they were seeing so many
OL,19,Fmore children with cancer because,
OL,20,Fthey say, of the impact the plant is
OL,21,Facutely having on children's health.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/17
