OL,3,CInside Italy's 'toxic town', where
OL,4,Cchildren grow up fearing cancer
OL,6,FSentieri, a government agency
OL,7,Finvestigating the link between health
OL,8,Fand the environment, concluded in 2023
OL,9,Fthat cancer rates are significantly
OL,10,Fhigher in the city than the rest of
OL,11,Fthe Puglia region.
OL,13,FIn adults, prostate and breast cancer
OL,14,Frates are above what would be expected.
OL,16,FCancer in newborns to 14-year-old
OL,17,Fchildren is more than 30% higher than
OL,18,Fthe rest of the region, and young
OL,19,Fadults aged 15-30 years old are twice
OL,20,Fas likely to get cancer if they live
OL,21,Fhere.
