OL,3,CInside Italy's 'toxic town', where
OL,4,Cchildren grow up fearing cancer
OL,6,FAlison told ITV News: "I think it's
OL,7,Freally soul-destroying to see the red
OL,8,Fdust causing issues like we've seen
OL,9,Fback in Corby. You know this is a land
OL,10,Fwhere people are laid to rest and yet
OL,11,Fthey're still getting covered."
OL,13,FTaranto's Ilva plant, which opened in
OL,14,Fthe mid-1960s, remains a major
OL,15,Femployer in the city, with 8,500
OL,16,Fworkers.
OL,18,FItalian journalist Federica Adriani
OL,19,Fconnected the families from Taranto
OL,20,Fand Corby, so they can share
OL,21,Finformation.
